<p>As stated by the standard laid down by The Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI), Internal Audit is largely defined as a Risk Management Function autonomously carried out to support the Management of an entity. It is performed internally at the request of the Management and poles apart from External or Statutory Audit.</p>

