<p>Propriety audit is based on the authentication of transactions in the best interest of public and normally established standards of conduct. The term &ldquo;propriety&rdquo; is defined finely to understand its purpose and end results. It says &ldquo;the &lsquo;propriety&rsquo; that meets the tests of public interest. It is standards of conduct and generally accepted customs, and mainly as valid to professional performance, necessities of government regulations and professional codes&rdquo;.</p>

